🚀 Data Science with Python: Complete Roadmap & Syllabus
This roadmap will guide you from beginner to expert in Data Science with Python, covering essential concepts, tools, and practical projects.
________________________________________
1️⃣ Introduction to Data Science
✅ What is Data Science?
✅ Data Science Lifecycle (CRISP-DM, OSEMN)
✅ Applications of Data Science (Healthcare, Finance, E-commerce, etc.)
✅ Overview of Python for Data Science
✅ Installing Python & Jupyter Notebook (Anaconda Setup)
________________________________________
2️⃣ Python Programming for Data Science
✅ Python Basics (Variables, Data Types, Loops, Functions)
✅ List, Tuple, Dictionary, Sets
✅ File Handling (CSV, JSON, Excel)
✅ Lambda Functions, Map, Filter, Reduce
✅ Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) in Python
✅ Working with APIs (REST API, JSON Handling)
________________________________________
3️⃣ Data Manipulation with Pandas & NumPy
✅ NumPy Basics (Arrays, Operations, Broadcasting)
✅ Pandas DataFrames & Series
✅ Data Cleaning & Preprocessing
✅ Handling Missing Data
✅ Merging, Joining & Grouping Data
✅ Pivot Tables & Reshaping Data
________________________________________
4️⃣ Data Visualization with Matplotlib & Seaborn
✅ Basic & Advanced Plots (Line, Bar, Scatter, Histogram)
✅ Customizing Plots (Titles, Legends, Annotations)
✅ Seaborn (Boxplot, Violin Plot, Heatmap, Pairplot)
✅ Interactive Visualizations with Plotly
________________________________________
5️⃣ Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
✅ Understanding Data Distributions
✅ Detecting Outliers & Skewness
✅ Feature Correlation Analysis
✅ Data Transformation & Encoding
✅ Feature Scaling (Normalization & Standardization)
________________________________________
6️⃣ Statistics & Probability for Data Science
✅ Measures of Central Tendency (Mean, Median, Mode)
✅ Variability (Variance, Standard Deviation)
✅ Probability Distributions (Normal, Poisson, Binomial)
✅ Hypothesis Testing (t-test, Chi-Square, ANOVA)
✅ Confidence Intervals & p-Values
________________________________________
7️⃣ Machine Learning with Scikit-Learn
✅ Introduction to Machine Learning (ML)
✅ Types of ML (Supervised, Unsupervised, Reinforcement Learning)
✅ Train-Test Split & Cross-Validation
✅ Performance Metrics (Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1-score, AUC-ROC)
✅ Model Selection & Evaluation
________________________________________
🔹 Supervised Learning (Regression & Classification)
✅ Regression Models:
•	Linear Regression
•	Polynomial Regression
•	Ridge & Lasso Regression
✅ Classification Models:
•	Logistic Regression
•	Decision Trees
•	Random Forest
•	Support Vector Machines (SVM)
•	K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)
•	Gradient Boosting (XGBoost, LightGBM, CatBoost)
________________________________________
🔹 Unsupervised Learning (Clustering & Dimensionality Reduction)
✅ Clustering Algorithms:
•	K-Means Clustering
•	Hierarchical Clustering
•	DBSCAN
✅ Dimensionality Reduction:
•	Principal Component Analysis (PCA)
•	t-SNE & UMAP
________________________________________
8️⃣ Feature Engineering & Model Tuning
✅ Feature Selection (Filter, Wrapper, Embedded Methods)
✅ Handling Imbalanced Data (SMOTE, Undersampling)
✅ Hyperparameter Tuning (Grid Search, Random Search)
________________________________________
9️⃣ Deep Learning with TensorFlow & Keras
✅ Introduction to Deep Learning & Neural Networks
✅ Building Artificial Neural Networks (ANN)
✅ Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) for Image Processing
✅ Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN) for Time Series Analysis
✅ Transfer Learning & Pretrained Models
________________________________________
🔟 Natural Language Processing (NLP)
✅ Tokenization & Text Preprocessing
✅ Stopword Removal & Lemmatization
✅ TF-IDF & Word Embeddings
✅ Sentiment Analysis
✅ Named Entity Recognition (NER)
✅ Transformers & Large Language Models (LLMs)
________________________________________
1️⃣1️⃣ Time Series Analysis
✅ Moving Averages & Exponential Smoothing
✅ ARIMA & SARIMA Models
✅ LSTMs for Time Series Forecasting
