✅ Model Serialization (Pickle, Joblib)
✅ CI/CD for ML Pipelines (Docker, Kubernetes)
✅ Monitoring ML Models in Production
________________________________________
1️⃣4️⃣ Data Science Projects & Case Studies
✅ Beginner: Exploratory Data Analysis (Titanic Dataset)
✅ Intermediate: Predicting House Prices (Regression)
✅ Advanced: Real-time Sentiment Analysis (NLP)
✅ Enterprise-Level: End-to-End ML Pipeline in Cloud
________________________________________
🛠 Tools & Technologies Covered
✅ Programming: Python (Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-Learn, TensorFlow, PyTorch)
✅ Data Handling: SQL, MongoDB, BigQuery
✅ Visualization: Matplotlib, Seaborn, Plotly, Power BI
✅ ML & DL: Scikit-learn, TensorFlow, Keras, PyTorch
✅ Big Data: Apache Spark, Hadoop, AWS S3
✅ Deployment: Flask, FastAPI, Docker, Kubernetes
________________________________________
🎯 Learning Path Recommendations
1️⃣ Start with Python Basics → Learn programming essentials
2️⃣ Master Data Handling & Visualization → Work with Pandas, NumPy, and Matplotlib
3️⃣ Understand Statistics & Probability → Build a strong mathematical foundation
4️⃣ Learn Machine Learning & Model Evaluation → Work with Scikit-Learn
5️⃣ Explore Deep Learning → Understand Neural Networks with TensorFlow & Keras
6️⃣ Work on Real-world Projects → Apply your knowledge to practical cases
7️⃣ Learn Big Data & Deployment → Work with PySpark, MLOps, and Cloud
________________________________________
This roadmap will help you become a Data Science expert using Python. Let me know if you need additional resources! 🚀

